Build frontend assets for Frappe apps.

Running 'weg build' is equivalent to 'weg build assets'.

Examples:
  weg build                    # Build all app assets
  weg build myapp              # Build specific app assets
  weg build --production       # Production build with minification
  weg build watch              # Watch mode for development
  weg build clear              # Clear built assets

Usage:
  weg build [app] [flags]
  weg build [command]

Available Commands:
  assets      Build app assets
  clear       Clear build cache and compiled assets
  watch       Watch and rebuild assets on change

Flags:
      --hard          Clean build, remove old bundles
  -h, --help          help for build
      --production    Production mode with minification
  -s, --site string   Site to build for

Global Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts

Use "weg build [command] --help" for more information about a command.
